Annotations for TestNg - Evaluated at runtime

Pre-requisites - @BeforeSuite, @BeforeTest, @BeforeClass @BeforeMethod
//first open browser
//prepare test data - username, password

actual steps - @Test
//enter username, password
//click submit
//verify whether you are able to login

post-cleanup - @AfterMethod, @AfterClass, @AfterTest, @AfterSuite
//take screenshot
//close the browser
//clear the test values in variable
//close the database
//close the files
//delete temporary files
//send an alert or email

Locators on WebPage
ID - Most Unique form of Locator. (Priority)
Name - Name of the element
className - their program names-- logical names
Link Text - Just check if it has <a> in html it is called anchor tag
Partial Link Text - <a> but if you know only partial text
Css - font, colour, text style... formatting properties of an element
Xpath - DOM Object (Document Object Model) XMl Path Expression
Text() - works with Xpath

Find an element using attribute and value
//Tag-name[@attribute='value']
Using Text
//Tag-name[text()='value']
Using Multiple attributes
//div[@class='value' and @a ='facebook.com']
//tag[text()='value and @a ='facebook.com']
Using Contains
//h2[contains(text(),'facebook']